oon, Leo L.M.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/588ff113edc72311fa9dd5494fe79544", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/74601fc28087c3b6597714b196ce9e6cf1c4027cca8f8abd89209265d810d01d", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/H6RBI8W9", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/H6RBI8W9", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/9698bb8e41cc560f6388fa9c387a54e6!/b84898-87227", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"title": "Current Opinion in Virology"}, "alternate_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/588ff113edc72311fa9dd5494fe79544"}, {"identifier": "urn:lsid:zotero.org:groups:5435545:items:H6RBI8W9"}, {"identifier": "10.1016/j.coviro.2011.10.013"}], "communities": [{"id": "batlit"}, {"id": "biosyslit"}], "relations": {"version": [{"index": 0, "is_last": true, "parent": {"pid_type": "recid", "pid_value": "13527357"}}]}}, "title": "Mass extinctions, biodiversity and mitochondrial function: Are bats 'special' as reservoirs for emerging viruses?", "links": {"self": "https://zenodo.org/api/records/13527358", "self_html": "https://zenodo.org/records/13527358", "preview_html": "https://zenodo.org/records/13527358?preview=1", "doi": "https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.13527358"